snippet: The 30 people arrested after a Greenpeace protest at a Russian oil rig in the Arctic were transferred to prisons in St. Petersburg on Tuesday.
abstract: Thirty people arrested after a Greenpeace protest at a Russian oil rig in the Arctic are transferred to prisons in St Petersburg, Russia.
lead_paragraph: The 30 people arrested after a Greenpeace protest at a Russian oil rig in the Arctic were transferred to prisons in St. Petersburg on Tuesday.

headline.main: Russia: Greenpeace Protesters Taken to St. Petersburg Prisons
